<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="sec-counting-add-multiply">
    <title>The Addition and Multiplication Principles of Counting</title>

    <objectives>
        <ol>
            <li><p>Understand when and how to use the Addition Principle of Counting</p></li>
            <li><p>Understand when and how to use the Multiplication Principle of Counting</p></li>
        </ol>
    </objectives>

    <exploration xml:id="exp-add-multiply">
        <introduction>
            <p>
                Suppose that a restaurant menu has 6 appetizers and 10 entrées. How many options do you have if
                <ol>
                    <li>you only order one dish, either an appetizer or an entrée?</li>
                    <li>you are hungry and will order both an appetizer and an entrée?</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            
        </introduction>
    </exploration>

    
</section>